A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Charles "Charlie" Kay Stevens; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Charles "Charlie" Kay Stevens on August 16, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Charles "Charlie" Kay Stevens was born on August 26, 1937, in Little River,
5 North Miami, Florida, a beloved son of Byron Post Stevens and Blanche Henrietta
6 Sparkman; and
7 WHEREAS, he served with honor as part of the United States Army from 1956 to 1958,
8 during which time he was stationed in Japan as an aerial photographer; and
9 WHEREAS, in 1962, Charlie relocated to Georgia and established Lea's Drive Inn in
10 Acworth, an entrepreneurial pursuit he expanded upon throughout his life by owning and
11 operating several additional restaurants, including The Corner Cafe in Dallas; and
